Aim
To write a Python program to demonstrate Object-Oriented Programming concepts such as class & object, inheritance (single, multilevel, multiple, hierarchical, hybrid), polymorphism, and method overriding.

Algorithm
Step 1: Start the program.
Step 2: Create a class Student with name and marks and display total marks.
Step 3: Implement Single Inheritance using Person → Student class.
Step 4: Implement Multilevel Inheritance using Person → Student → Result.
Step 5: Implement Multiple Inheritance using HR and Salary classes inherited by Employee.
Step 6: Implement Hierarchical Inheritance using Bank → Savings and Current classes.
Step 7: Implement Hybrid Inheritance using Company, Employee, Manager, and Details classes.
Step 8: Implement Polymorphism (Method Overloading) using same method with different parameters.
Step 9: Implement Method Overriding using parent and child classes.
Step 10: Display outputs for all concepts.
Step 11: Stop the program.
